<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD1AF28C9DE9BE5FB4F9462" pageId="4" pageNumber="567" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD1AF28C9DE9BE5FB8395AA" blockId="4.[151,1436,150,285]" box="[199,1070,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD1AF28C9DE9BE5FEE395AA" bold="true" box="[199,334,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to its projected anterior pronotal angles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD1AF28C9DE9B80FB4F9462" blockId="4.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD1AF28C9DE9B80FE629587" bold="true" box="[199,463,222,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Amber mine located near Noije Bum Village, Tanai Township, Myitkyina District, 
<collectingRegion id="49B6E4B9FFD1AF28C98E9A5DFE879462" box="[151,298,259,285]" country="Myanmar" name="Kachin" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Kachin State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3656ACBFFD1AF28C82C9A5DFE0B9462" box="[309,422,259,285]" name="Myanmar" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
; unnamed horizon, mid-Cretaceous, Upper Albian to Lower Cenomanian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
