<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD1AF29C9DE9CE9FEF29586" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="4" pageNumber="567" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD1AF29C9DE9CE9FEF29586" blockId="4.[151,1436,1975,2037]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD1AF28C9DE9CE9FEEF92AE" bold="true" box="[199,322,1975,2001]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lateral sides of clypeus subparallel in anterior half (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD1AF28CA889CE9FC4192AE" box="[913,1004,1975,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Left mandible with three apical teeth and two moderately separated teeth on incisor edge (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD1AF28CBEB9C85FCE3928A" box="[754,846,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Penultimate maxillary palpomere about as long as apical one (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C8009BC9FE2395CE" box="[281,398,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4A,D</figureCitation>
). Jugal processes asymmetrical, comparatively long; right process longer than left one; inner sides with a tooth (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C8699BE5FE6195AA" box="[368,460,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Median groove of pronotum probably absent (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CAF49BE5FBEB95AA" box="[1005,1094,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Anterior angles of pronotum pointed (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C9E29B81FEFF9586" box="[251,338,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD0AF29C9DE9A5CFD9A96DA" pageId="5" pageNumber="568" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD0AF29C9DE9A5CFB889462" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,1061,258,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD0AF29C9DE9A5CFEF49463" bold="true" box="[199,345,258,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Description.</emphasis>
Body elongate and flattened, about 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD0AF29CBF79A5CFCE99462" box="[750,836,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="568" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD0AF29CA939A5DFC4D9462" box="[906,992,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="568" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD0AF29C9DE9A79FB4E97FA" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
Head (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C80B9A79FE29943E" box="[274,388,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,260,1723,1749]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-61@4.[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytral apex, dorsal view. D, Pterothorax, ventral view. E, Abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; jp, jugular process; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457408/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 3A,B</figureCitation>
) prognathous, constricted posteriorly, with distinct neck region. Temples distinctly projected posterolaterally. Eyes small, round and finely facetted, without interfacetal setae. Antennal insertions slightly concealed from above; subantennal grooves absent. Frontoclypeal suture not clearly discerned. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CC1D9A31FAF194F6" box="[1284,1372,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) with lateral sides subparallel (or weakly diverging) in anterior portion; anterior margin truncate. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CC1E9ACDFACD94D2" box="[1287,1376,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) narrowed anteriorly, apically truncate, with numerous elongate setae. Antennae 11-segmented, moniliform, with weak, 3-segmented club. Mandibles (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C8EF9A85FDFD948A" box="[502,592,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) tridentate apically; left mandible with two moderately separated teeth on incisor edge; right mandible with one blunt tooth on incisor edge. Maxillary palps (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CD2C9AA1FB219766" box="[1077,1164,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) probably 4-segmented; palpomere 1 short; palpomere 2 elongate; palpomere 3 longer than wide, distinctly longer than half length of apical one. 
<collectingRegion id="49B6E4B9FFD0AF29C9D69919FE83971E" box="[207,302,583,609]" country="Myanmar" name="Chin" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Mentum</collectingRegion>
strongly transverse. Jugal processes (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CBC49919FC9B971E" box="[733,822,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical; inner sides with a tooth; right process longer than left one, strongly constricted above tooth; left process weakly constricted above tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD0AF29C9DE99D1FE239646" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
Pronotal disc (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C87199D1FE1197D6" box="[360,444,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) longer than wide; anterior angles pointed laterally; median groove not clearly discerned. Prosternal process (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C86C99EDFE6097B2" box="[373,461,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) wide, expanding beyond procoxae and meeting broad postcoxal projections, apically truncate. Procoxal cavities (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C8CA9989FD86978E" box="[467,555,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) circular, widely separated. Elytra (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CADA9989FBB7978E" box="[963,1050,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,260,1723,1749]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-61@4.[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytral apex, dorsal view. D, Pterothorax, ventral view. E, Abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; jp, jugular process; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457408/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) about 2.2 times as long as width combined; surface with longitudinal carinae. Mesoventrite (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CA3799A5FC2E966A" box="[814,899,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) relatively narrow. Mesocoxal cavities (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29CC2699A5FA39966A" box="[1343,1428,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) moderately separated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD0AF29C9DE981DFD9A96DA" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD0AF29C817981DFECE9622" box="[270,355,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,260,1841,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-323@5.[151,1436,954,1816]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mouthparts, dorsal view. E, Prothorax, dorsal view. F, Fore leg. Abbreviations: an, antenna; cl, clypeus; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) short. Femora distally with groove on inner side. Tibiae shorter than femora, widened apically with spinose outer apical angle; spurs large and stout, paired on all legs. Tarsi 4-4-4; tarsomeres simple, without ventral lobes. Pretarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
